modules.description: This module converts durations (stored as nanoseconds in a 64-bit unsigned integer) to and from time units like microseconds, seconds, days, and floating-point values, ensuring precise time calculations. It provides integer and floating-point extraction functions for specific units, such as hours, years, or seconds, while enforcing input validity through exceptions. Use cases include time-based scheduling, duration formatting, and cross-unit arithmetic in systems requiring high-resolution timing.
